Fatty acids are part and parcel in TDG. Nowadays, a variety of fatty acids and volatile oils have been identified in TDG, mainly including lacceroic acid (65), succinic acid (66), palmitic acid (67), oleic acid (68), linoleic acid (69), stearic acid (70), myristic acid (71), margaric acid (72), pentadecylic acid (73) and methyl linolenate (74), psoralen (75), camphor (76), 2, 3-butanediol (77), hexanoic acid (78), benzyl alcohol (79), benzeneethanol (80), phenol (81), 6, 10, 14-trimethyl-2-pentadecanone (82), cumene (83), diphenylamine (84), arachidic acid (85), linolenic acid (86), azelaic acid (87) (
 Liu, 2000; 
 Huo et al., 2008; 
 Hu et al., 2013; 
 Ding et al., 2015b). 
 Xu et al. (2017) isolate a long-chain polyene unsaturated fatty acid component, three kinds of monoterpenes and one kind of phenylpropanoids from the extraction site of petroleum ether, which are 9-hydroxy-10,12-octadecadienoic acid (88), (4R, 5R)-4-Hydroxy-2-methyl-5-propan-2-ylcyclohex-2-en-1-one (89), (4S, 5R)-4-Hydroxy-2-methyl-5-propan-2-ylcyclohex-2-en-1-one (90), (3R, 4R, 6S)-3, 6-dihydroxy-1-menthylene, cinnamic acid (91), respectively. The chemical structures of volatile oil and fatty acids are shown in 

